.TH DHCONSOLE 1 "July 2026" "DigiHub" "DigiHub User Manual"
.SH NAME
dhconsole \- turn DigiHub's web console (ttyd + login) on or off
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dhconsole
.BR on | off | status
.br
.B dhconsole
[\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dhconsole
enables, disables, or reports the status of the
.B dhconsole.service
systemd unit (see
.BR dhconsoled (1)),
which gives a full terminal in the browser, authenticated with the
operator's real system username and password (checked by PAM via
.BR login (1),
exactly like a serial console or SSH session) rather than anything
DigiHub\-specific.
.PP
Like
.BR dhrig (1),
.BR dhpat (1),
.BR dhardop (1),
and
.BR dhwebchat (1),
.B dhconsole
is a simple independent toggle, not part of
.BR dhmode (1)'s
mutually\-exclusive digital mode set, and doesn't touch
.IR $HOME/.dhinfo .
Off by default, same as the others \-\- turning it on only starts the
listener; nobody gets a shell without authenticating.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B on
Install (if needed)/enable/start
.BR dhconsole.service .
.TP
.B off
Stop and disable
.BR dhconsole.service .
.TP
.B status
Print the service's current systemd state
.RI ( active ,
.IR inactive ,
etc.) and exit. Read\-only.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display this help information and exit.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Turn the web console on:
.B dhconsole on
.TP
Turn it off:
.B dhconsole off
.TP
Check whether it's running:
.B dhconsole status
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/dhconsole.service
Installed on first
.B "dhconsole on" .
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
The requested action completed, or help was displayed.
.TP
.B 1
.B ttyd
is not installed (for
.BR on ).
.TP
.B 2
An unknown action was supplied (not
.IR on ,
.IR off ,
or
.IR status ).
